SIMPLE: generally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Generally
<hw>Gen"er*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In general;
commonly; extensively, though not universally; most
frequently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a general way, or in general relation; in the
main; upon the whole; comprehensively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Generally</qex> speaking, they live very quietly.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Collectively; as a whole; without omissions.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I counsel that all Israel be <qex>generally</qex> gathered unto
thee.</q> <rj><qau>2 Sam. xvii. ll.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Generalness</ent>⟦br⟧
